
'''= "eventology is the opposite of nomadology", it's the opposite of circular time [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TlslKAyl70I Alexander Bard]'''

=Discussion=

Cadell Last:

* "Nomadological societies were based on the repetition of the same in the child to elder, child to elder, child to elder.  There was an unconscious presupposition that this would continue on forever and ever.

* Eventological societies were based on the repetition with difference in the child to elder, child to elder, child to ender (i.e. that there would be a difference between the generations).  The most extreme difference gets reified in religious structures as the “end times” (i.e. the child as the ultimate event)."

(https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-3-030-46966-5, chapters 8 to 10)

